definition: to begin/to set one's hand to
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]
hand/(formal) to hold/person engaged in certain types of work/person skilled in certain types of work/personal(ly)/convenient/classifier for skill/CL:雙|双[shuang1],隻|只[zhi1]

sentences.english: Start with high-level conceptual and visual design.

sentences.english: Starting with researches of Dialect itself, the linguistic thinking of Yangxiong is discussed.
sentences.chinese: 从《方言》本身的研究入手，探讨了扬雄的语言思想。

sentences.english: To perform a piece of music on flutes, nine requirements must be met.
sentences.chinese: 要完美地演奏一首笛曲需要从九个方面入手。

sentences.english: Having fewer children to accomplish emissions reduction, it is really a topic ahead of its time.

sentences.english: Beginned with basic knowledge of fluorescence, fluorescence microscope characteristics are briefly described.

sentences.english: This article has obtained from the behavior region theory, carrying on the discussion to the new region factor.

sentences.english: The research on the civilian community helped Mark set the starting point of the theroy of historical materialism.

sentences.english: However, the example gives you enough information to start with.
sentences.chinese: 然而，这个示例为您入手提供了足够的信息。

sentences.english: It is with such facts that a scientific investigation must begin.

The shift of perspectives in the study of ci fu can be viewed from three aspects.

sentences.english: Taiping Jing should be understood and illustrated from the angle of medical science.
sentences.chinese: 从医药学的角度入手，解读和阐释《太平经》。

sentences.english: To work out a plan, one has to start with investigation.
